# Frontend Stack Rules

- Use the latest stable React release with TypeScript for all frontend additions.
- Keep UI operational and clear; functionality and correctness take priority over visual polish.
- Implement required dashboard behavior: risk table, loading/error states, and trigger-action workflow.
- Keep components small and composable; lift shared data-fetching logic into hooks/services when useful.
- Use accessible, understandable risk tier visuals (`high/medium/low`) and clear signal explanations.
- Validate and surface API failures gracefully so property managers can recover quickly.
